# Testing and Commit Gates

## Testing Requirements
- Add unit tests for new or changed logic.
- Add e2e tests for critical user flows:
  - auth
  - first-login onboarding
  - dashboard content rendering
  - voting interactions
- Require all tests to pass before considering work complete.
- Keep test structure readable and maintainable.
- Execute tests slice-by-slice according to `docs/roadmap.md` checkpoints.
- Minimum per slice: at least one acceptance test (unit or e2e) that proves the slice goal.
- For provider and dashboard work, include failure-path tests (timeout, fallback, partial success).

## Gotcha Tracking
- Save gotcha moments during development, including:
  - external API reliability/rate-limit issues
  - auth/session edge cases
  - flaky test behavior and stabilizing notes

## Commit Workflow
- Follow `.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc` for phase/TODO branching, commit size, and message format.
- One logical change per commit; split large work instead of one big commit.
- Ask user permission before committing unless they explicitly requested it.
- Subject line max 72 characters; add a short body when the why is not obvious.
- Keep each TODO branch aligned to one roadmap slice; merge into the phase branch only after tests pass.
- Do not merge a phase branch into `master` without explicit user approval.
